===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|水|咸|alt1=氵|ls=ic|ls2=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=water|t2=seal}} - to seal off a stream of water, decreasing its flow. {{m|zh|咸|tr=-}} is the original character of {{m|zh|緘|tr=-}} and also serves as a semantic component.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|s=减|t2=减}}
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} adduces no potential cognates and leaves the origin open. That said, note strong similarities to {{cog|tbq-pro|*s-grum|t=contracted, stunted, dwarfish}}, whence {{cog|my|ကျုံ့|t=to shrink, contract}}.

